{"word":"ἐδωδή","slug":"ἐδωδή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐδωδή</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἔδω'><el>ἔδω</el></a>\n<el>(ἐδωδή, ἡ,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>food, meat, victuals</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>fodder</i> for cattle, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a bait</i> for fish, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}